<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <title>Information dashboard</title>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="stylesheets/util.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="stylesheets/main.css">

</head>

<body>

    <div class="limiter">
        <div class="container-login100">
            <div class="wrap-login100">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <img src="images/logo.png" style="display: block;
							margin-left: auto;
							margin-right: auto;
							">
                </div>
                <form>

                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Id: <%= bloodDetail.invoice_no %></label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Blood Type: <%= bloodDetail.blood_type %> </label>
                    </div>

                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Collected Date: <%= bloodDetail.collected_date %></label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Expiry Date: <%= bloodDetail.expiry_date %></label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Blood Group: <%= bloodDetail.blood_group %></label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Hospital's Name: <%= bloodDetail.hospital_name %></label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Patient's Name: <%= bloodDetail.patient_name %> </label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group row">
                        <label for="staticEmail" class="col-sm-3 col-form-label">Purpose: <%= bloodDetail.purpose %></label>
                    </div>
                    <br />

                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="container">
                            <div class="col-md-12">

                                <% if(bloodDetail.blood_type === 'Plasma'){ %>
                                <h3>Plasma :</h3>
                                <label class="col-form-label">Plasma contains about 7% vital proteins such as albumin, gamma globulin and
                                    anti-hemophilic factor, and 1% mineral salts, sugars, fats, hormones and vitamins,
                                    about 92% water.</label>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Color:</strong>Yellowish</li>
                                    <li><strong>Shelf Life:</strong> 1 Year</li>
                                    <li><strong>Storage Conditions: </strong>Frozen</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Uses:</strong>: Burn patients, Shock, Bleeding disorders
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Plasma is obtained by separating the liquid portion of blood from the cells.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Plasma is frozen within 24 hours of being donated in order to preserve the
                                        valuable clotting factors.</li>
                                    <li>Plasma is commonly transfused to trauma, burn and shock patients, as well as
                                        people with severe liver disease or multiple clotting factor deficiencies.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <% } else if(bloodDetail.blood_type === 'Fresh'){ %>
                                <h3>Fresh Blood:</h3>
                                <label class="col-form-label">The blood supplies oxygen to cells and tissues providing essential nutrients to
                                    cells.</label>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Color:</strong>Red</li>
                                    <li><strong>Shelf Life:</strong> Should be used within 6 hours</li>
                                    <li><strong>Storage Conditions: </strong>Refrigerated</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Uses:</strong>: Trauma, Surgery</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <ul>
                                    <li>They help in removing waste such as carbon dioxide, urea, and lactic acid.</li>
                                    <li>It regulates pH, temperature, water content of cells.</li>
                                    <li>Protects against blood loss through clotting.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <% } else if(bloodDetail.blood_type === 'Whole'){ %>
                                    <h3 >Whole Blood :</h3>
                                    <label class="col-form-label">Whole blood contains red cells, white cells, and platelets (~45% of volume) suspended
                                        in blood plasma (~55% of volume).</label>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Color:</strong>Red</li>
                                        <li><strong>Shelf Life:</strong> 21/35 days*</li>
                                        <li><strong>Storage Conditions: </strong>Refrigerated</li>
                                        <li><strong>Key Uses:</strong>: Trauma, Surgery</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>It is the Simplest, most common type of blood donation.</li>
                                        <li>It is the most flexible because it can be transfused in its original form.</li>
                                        <li>It can be refrigerated for up to 35 days.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                <% } else{ %>
                                <h3>White Blood Cells:</h3>
                                <label class="col-form-label">White blood cells, or leukocytes, are one of the body's defense against disease.some
                                    destroy bacteria and others create antibodies against bacteria and viruses or fight
                                    malignant disease.</label>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Color:</strong>Colourless</li>
                                    <li><strong>Shelf Life:</strong> Should be used within 24 hours</li>
                                    <li><strong>Storage Conditions: </strong>Refrigerated</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Uses:</strong>: Trauma, Surgery</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <ul>
                                    <li>They are an important part of the immune system.</li>
                                    <li>These cells help fight infections by attacking bacteria, viruses, and germs that
                                        invade the body</li>
                                    <li>They are originated in the bone marrow but circulate throughout the bloodstream.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <h3>Red Blood cells :</h3>
                                <label class="col-form-label">Red blood cells are prepared from whole blood by removing the plasma (the liquid
                                    portion of the blood).</label>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Color:</strong>Red</li>
                                    <li><strong>Shelf Life:</strong>Up to 42 days*</li>
                                    <li><strong>Storage Conditions: </strong>Refrigerated</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Uses:</strong>: Trauma, Surgery, Anemia, Any blood loss, Blood
                                        disorders, such as sickle cell.
                                
                                </ul>
                                
                                <ul>
                                    <li>RBCs are used to treat anemia without substantially increasing the patientâ€™s
                                        blood volume.</li>
                                    <li>Leukocyte-reduced RBCs are prepared by removing leukocytes (white blood cells)
                                        by filtration shortly after donation.</li>
                                    <li>Patients who benefit most from transfusion of red blood cells include those with
                                        chronic anemia resulting from kidney failure or gastrointestinal bleeding, and
                                        those with acute blood loss resulting from trauma.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <% } %>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>